Cell.Data: Defines the level of expectation associated with a given system capability.

If "SHALL NOT" is desired, use the "prohibited" modifier extension. This extension should only be used with conformance profiles documenting requirements, not those documenting actual system capabilities
If set to true, indicates that support for the specified behavior would make a system non=conformant with the specification
Code system not defined in a value set
A code system that is supported by the system that is not defined in a value set resource
Typically, this is a large terminology such as LOINC, SNOMED CT
A container for a single allowable parameter combination
Some systems have complex search rules imposed by the data structurea nd/or business rules. This extension allows these rules to be represented

If a search combination is specified, clients should expect that they must submit that required combination or the search will be unsuccesful. If multiple search parameter combinations are specified, a client may pick between them, and supply the minimal required parameters for any of the combinations.
A search parameter name in the combination which is required
A search parameter name in the combination which is optional

If a defined parameter is not listed as a required or optional parameter, the implication is that the parameter is not supported with this combination. Servers may ignore It, though some may return an error if it is used
